WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:11.185 --> 00:00:14.188
Previously on Bull...
There's something

2
00:00:14.231 --> 00:00:15.841
I have to tell you.
Henri is married.

3
00:00:15.885 --> 00:00:18.148
That doesn't make any sense.

4
00:00:18.192 --> 00:00:20.585
We separated five years ago.

5
00:00:20.629 --> 00:00:23.371
but in the midst of the divorce.
she was diagnosed with MS.

6
00:00:23.414 --> 00:00:25.851
so we decided
to stay married

7
00:00:25.895 --> 00:00:28.550
so she could stay
on my health insurance.

8
00:00:28.593 --> 00:00:29.812
I'm sorry.

9
00:00:29.855 --> 00:00:31.683
How did you find out?

10
00:00:31.727 --> 00:00:33.250
I did a background check
on you.

11
00:00:33.294 --> 00:00:34.991
I guess neither of us
is having lunch today.

12
00:00:35.035 --> 00:00:36.601
Henri. I...

13
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:44.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

14
00:01:14.596 --> 00:01:16.641
We've been over this.
You know who to watch out for.

15
00:01:16.685 --> 00:01:19.209
Gatsby's Greatest.
He's a stalker.
Got it.

16
00:01:19.253 --> 00:01:21.037
And Rebel With A Cause shoots
out the gate like a bullet.

17
00:01:21.081 --> 00:01:22.865
Lauren. I've got this.

18
00:01:22.908 --> 00:01:24.171
Give 'em a run for their money.

19
00:01:25.476 --> 00:01:28.262
Rafael? Rafael?

20
00:01:28.305 --> 00:01:30.438
You need to take
a breathalyzer test right now.

21
00:01:30.481 --> 00:01:32.266
What?

22
00:01:32.309 --> 00:01:34.311
You need
to take a breathalyzer test.

23
00:01:34.355 --> 00:01:36.313
Someone reported you
drinking in your truck.

24
00:01:36.357 --> 00:01:37.880
Raf. is this true?

25
00:01:37.923 --> 00:01:40.056
No. No. that's ridiculous.

26
00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:42.058
I can smell it on you. Raf.

27
00:01:48.891 --> 00:01:50.632
It was only one drink.

28
00:01:50.675 --> 00:01:51.850
It's never just one.

29
00:01:53.896 --> 00:01:56.681
You're fired.No. no. no. no.
Please. Mr. Sinclair.

30
00:01:56.725 --> 00:01:58.030
Look. I'll win.
Okay. Bold Spirit and me--

31
00:01:58.074 --> 00:01:59.293
we have a good thing going.

32
00:01:59.336 --> 00:02:01.077
You ride Bold Spirit drunk.

33
00:02:01.121 --> 00:02:02.470
you could injure him.
You ever think of that?

34
00:02:02.513 --> 00:02:04.950
Get him the hell out of here.
No!

35
00:02:04.994 --> 00:02:07.431
No. Look...Come on.

36
00:02:07.475 --> 00:02:09.085
How could you do this?

37
00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:10.695
After all the races
I've won for you?!

38
00:02:12.132 --> 00:02:14.003
You'll regret this.
you hear me?!

39
00:02:14.046 --> 00:02:16.179
And they're off!

40
00:02:16.223 --> 00:02:18.138
Slides Truly bursting through
the gate. taking an early lead.

41
00:02:18.181 --> 00:02:20.140
Why Certainly moves
from the back of the pack

42
00:02:20.183 --> 00:02:22.098
passing Genuine Affinity
on the outside!

43
00:02:23.099 --> 00:02:25.057
Get your hands off me!

44
00:02:27.495 --> 00:02:28.974
This isn't fair!

45
00:02:29.975 --> 00:02:31.803
Bold Spirit needs me!

46
00:03:09.145 --> 00:03:10.973
Put a hose on that!

47
00:03:13.149 --> 00:03:14.890
If you think of anything else...

48
00:03:18.154 --> 00:03:20.983
Bold Spirit. Is he okay?

49
00:03:21.026 --> 00:03:23.246
Sorry. honey.
He's gone.

50
00:03:23.290 --> 00:03:26.162
Get those hoses
to the back of the barn!

51
00:03:27.032 --> 00:03:28.382
How did this happen?!

52
00:03:28.425 --> 00:03:30.166
Sir. please stand back.

53
00:03:30.210 --> 00:03:32.951
It's worse
than just Bold Spirit.

54
00:03:32.995 --> 00:03:34.170
What do you mean?

55
00:03:35.693 --> 00:03:37.826
Oh. my God. Oh. no. Lauren.

56
00:03:37.869 --> 00:03:40.002
They found her in his stall.

57
00:03:40.045 --> 00:03:41.525
Oh. no!

58
00:03:41.569 --> 00:03:43.310
Can you tell me
what this woman was doing

59
00:03:43.353 --> 00:03:45.181
in the barn so late at night?

60
00:03:45.225 --> 00:03:49.054
Lauren is
Bold Spirit's trainer.

61
00:03:49.098 --> 00:03:51.231
We were worried
he had colic.

62
00:03:51.274 --> 00:03:53.407
We asked her to...

63
00:03:53.450 --> 00:03:55.409
keep an eye on him overnight.
Sarge?

64
00:03:55.452 --> 00:03:57.672
Go ahead.

65
00:03:57.715 --> 00:04:00.283
We found someone passed out
in a truck on the property.

66
00:04:06.985 --> 00:04:08.291
Sir?

67
00:04:10.032 --> 00:04:10.989
Come on.
Out of the truck.

68
00:04:13.601 --> 00:04:14.558
Sir.
What's going on?

69
00:04:14.602 --> 00:04:15.690
Sir. what's your name?

70
00:04:15.733 --> 00:04:17.257
Rafael Ramirez.

71
00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:18.562
You son of a bitch!

72
00:04:18.606 --> 00:04:19.694
Hey. hey. hey!
Oh.

73
00:04:19.737 --> 00:04:21.609
I need you
to step back.

74
00:04:21.652 --> 00:04:23.001
How could you do this?!

75
00:04:31.096 --> 00:04:32.794
Iz. it's your phone.

76
00:04:32.837 --> 00:04:34.709
Mm. what?

77
00:04:34.752 --> 00:04:36.276
It's your phone that's ringing.

78
00:04:39.714 --> 00:04:42.325
It's Rikers.
What?

79
00:04:42.369 --> 00:04:44.066
Hello?
Collect call from Rikers.

80
00:04:44.109 --> 00:04:45.633
Yeah. yeah.
I'll accept the charges.

81
00:04:45.676 --> 00:04:47.678
What's going on?

82
00:04:47.722 --> 00:04:51.334
Raf. okay. okay. okay. Okay.
Calm down. slow down. Slow down.

83
00:04:53.684 --> 00:04:55.469
Okay. Vamos a resolver esto.
Yo voy para allá ahora mismo.

84
00:04:55.512 --> 00:04:56.905
Gracias.

85
00:04:56.948 --> 00:04:58.559
What is it you were saying?

86
00:04:58.602 --> 00:05:00.648
It's. uh. Raf. the kid
that I used to mentor.

87
00:05:00.691 --> 00:05:03.303
Yeah. The jockey.
What's he doing at Rikers?

88
00:05:03.346 --> 00:05:06.480
There was a fire. and
the police think that he did it.

89
00:05:06.523 --> 00:05:08.569
Uh. I just...
I-I have to go help him.

90
00:05:08.612 --> 00:05:10.919
You're not going there.
It's 4:00 in the morning.

91
00:05:10.962 --> 00:05:12.442
No. I'm going.
and you're coming with me.

92
00:05:12.486 --> 00:05:14.618
No. I'm not.

93
00:05:14.662 --> 00:05:17.186
How long has it been
since you saw this kid?

94
00:05:17.229 --> 00:05:20.102
I don't know.
Uh. two years ago.

95
00:05:20.145 --> 00:05:22.322
I don't know.
It's been way too long.

96
00:05:22.365 --> 00:05:24.715
He did so much
to change his life around.

97
00:05:24.759 --> 00:05:27.283
Whatever... God.
whatever they think he did.

98
00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:29.720
there has to be some type
of mistake. I have to help him.

99
00:05:29.764 --> 00:05:32.332
Yes. I know it's a mistake.
and you will help him.

100
00:05:32.375 --> 00:05:35.073
but it is 4:00
in the morning.

101
00:05:35.117 --> 00:05:36.248
and Rikers doesn't
accept visitors

102
00:05:36.292 --> 00:05:37.772
until 8:00. so...

103
00:05:37.815 --> 00:05:39.295
I can't just let Raf sit there
all alone.

104
00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.906
I have to at least
try to get in.

105
00:05:41.950 --> 00:05:44.692
What do you want me to do? Call
Taylor and have her take Astrid

106
00:05:44.735 --> 00:05:47.912
so that we can go to Rikers
at 4:00 in the morning?

107
00:05:47.956 --> 00:05:49.131
Thank you.

108
00:05:49.174 --> 00:05:50.915
What?!

109
00:05:50.959 --> 00:05:53.657
I didn't burn down that stable.
I swear.

110
00:05:53.701 --> 00:05:55.877
We know you didn't.

111
00:05:55.920 --> 00:05:57.182
Whose stable was it?

112
00:05:57.226 --> 00:05:59.968
The man I used to work for--

113
00:06:00.011 --> 00:06:02.405
guy named Garrett Sinclair.
You used to work for him.

114
00:06:02.449 --> 00:06:03.928
So what happened?
You got fired?

115
00:06:03.972 --> 00:06:05.713
Yeah.

116
00:06:05.756 --> 00:06:07.976
Right before the third
at Belport yesterday.

117
00:06:08.019 --> 00:06:09.369
Why?

118
00:06:09.412 --> 00:06:10.544
He thought I'd been drinking.

119
00:06:10.587 --> 00:06:11.980
And had you?

120
00:06:12.023 --> 00:06:12.937
Jason.
No. it's...

121
00:06:12.981 --> 00:06:14.765
it's okay.

122
00:06:16.463 --> 00:06:18.029
Yes.

123
00:06:18.073 --> 00:06:20.380
I got super drunk
last night.

124
00:06:20.423 --> 00:06:21.816
Raf.

125
00:06:21.859 --> 00:06:25.036
I'd been sober
for almost four years.

126
00:06:25.080 --> 00:06:29.258
but. um. a couple months back.
Mariella broke things off.

127
00:06:29.301 --> 00:06:31.391
I guess between the breakup

128
00:06:31.434 --> 00:06:34.045
and getting fired.
I-I went on a...

129
00:06:34.089 --> 00:06:36.004
a bit of a bender.

130
00:06:36.047 --> 00:06:39.181
So. Rafael. someone is dead.
and the prosecution is gonna say

131
00:06:39.224 --> 00:06:42.184
that you are a drunk
who got fired

132
00:06:42.227 --> 00:06:44.186
and wanted revenge
on your former boss.

133
00:06:44.229 --> 00:06:46.188
It's-it's not like that.

134
00:06:46.231 --> 00:06:47.407
What's it like?Tell us.

135
00:06:47.450 --> 00:06:48.538
Everything from the beginning.

136
00:06:49.844 --> 00:06:52.629
Look. I-I know it sounds stupid.

137
00:06:52.673 --> 00:06:55.719
but I went to Bridleright to beg
Mr. Sinclair for my job back.

138
00:06:55.763 --> 00:06:57.155
It seemed like
a good idea

139
00:06:57.199 --> 00:06:58.548
after a bottle of vodka.

140
00:06:58.592 --> 00:07:00.420
But when I got there.

141
00:07:00.463 --> 00:07:01.856
the stable was on fire.

142
00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:03.161
What happened to your hands?

143
00:07:04.162 --> 00:07:06.426
I tried to open the doors.

144
00:07:06.469 --> 00:07:09.385
Bold Spirit was inside.
I had to save him.

145
00:07:09.429 --> 00:07:11.431
But the heat--

146
00:07:11.474 --> 00:07:12.823
it was too much.

147
00:07:12.867 --> 00:07:15.391
It was... awful.

148
00:07:15.435 --> 00:07:17.306
I-I couldn't...
It's okay. Raf.

149
00:07:17.349 --> 00:07:20.004
I'm sure you did
everything you could.

150
00:07:20.048 --> 00:07:21.658
Why didn't you call for help?

151
00:07:21.702 --> 00:07:23.007
My phone was dead.

152
00:07:24.313 --> 00:07:26.228
The last thing I remember
was heading to the house

153
00:07:26.271 --> 00:07:27.795
to get the Sinclairs.

154
00:07:27.838 --> 00:07:30.450
But I-I must have driven
in a ditch or something.

155
00:07:30.493 --> 00:07:32.452
because the next thing I know.

156
00:07:32.495 --> 00:07:34.410
a police officer's pulling me
out of my truck.

157
00:07:34.454 --> 00:07:35.977
Are you sure that's
the whole story?

158
00:07:36.020 --> 00:07:37.108
Yes.

159
00:07:39.546 --> 00:07:41.765
You-you know I'd never do this.

160
00:07:41.809 --> 00:07:44.507
I believe you.
I'm here.

161
00:07:44.551 --> 00:07:47.118
We're here to help.

162
00:07:47.162 --> 00:07:48.424
Here's what we're gonna do.

163
00:07:49.643 --> 00:07:52.080
I am gonna call
the executive director

164
00:07:52.123 --> 00:07:54.691
of the public defender's office
and see if he can help us.

165
00:07:54.735 --> 00:07:56.084
What?

166
00:07:56.127 --> 00:07:58.173
He owes me a favor.
and I'm sure

167
00:07:58.216 --> 00:08:01.045
he can arrange one of his best
attorneys to be on your case.

168
00:08:01.089 --> 00:08:03.265
Can I speak to you outside?

169
00:08:14.842 --> 00:08:16.800
I thought you came here
to help him.

170
00:08:16.844 --> 00:08:19.673
Rafael needs someone
to negotiate a plea deal.

171
00:08:19.716 --> 00:08:21.326
and that is what
public defenders do.

172
00:08:21.370 --> 00:08:23.241
He doesn't need a plea deal.
He's innocent.

173
00:08:23.285 --> 00:08:25.069
He needs you
to prove that.

174
00:08:25.113 --> 00:08:27.507
This is a system case.
and the public defender's office

175
00:08:27.550 --> 00:08:28.899
is gonna give him
a good defense.

176
00:08:28.943 --> 00:08:31.641
Rafael has been
in the system his entire life.

177
00:08:31.685 --> 00:08:33.556
I don't want him
in the system this time.

178
00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:35.253
You think he's guilty.
and that's why

179
00:08:35.297 --> 00:08:36.951
you've been interrogating him
the whole time.

180
00:08:36.994 --> 00:08:37.865
He was found drunk at
the scene of the crime.

181
00:08:37.908 --> 00:08:39.780
He has a hell of a motive.

182
00:08:39.823 --> 00:08:40.998
It certainly looks like he did it.
He didn't do it.

183
00:08:42.478 --> 00:08:45.525
I know him.
He is not capable.

184
00:08:45.568 --> 00:08:48.266
You know him sober.
but when a person is drunk.

185
00:08:48.310 --> 00:08:50.268
they are capable of doing things
you never see coming.

186
00:08:50.312 --> 00:08:52.662
No. I've known him
since he was 14.

187
00:08:52.706 --> 00:08:54.882
I know his soul.

188
00:08:54.925 --> 00:08:57.972
He's not vengeful.
He's not... he's not violent.

189
00:08:58.015 --> 00:09:00.583
He doesn't have a case.
Plea deal's the best option.

190
00:09:00.627 --> 00:09:04.674
No. His best option is for TAC
to prove that he's innocent.

191
00:09:04.718 --> 00:09:06.763
And I'm willing to pay for it.

192
00:09:06.807 --> 00:09:08.765
Oh. come on. Izzy.
This isn't about the money.
No.

193
00:09:08.809 --> 00:09:11.115
I am hiring TAC
and posting his bail.

194
00:09:11.159 --> 00:09:13.683
and you are taking this case.
Jason. and that's the end of it.

195
00:09:13.727 --> 00:09:14.945
I will see you inside.

196
00:09:15.946 --> 00:09:18.035
Good talk.

197
00:09:18.079 --> 00:09:20.124
♪

198
00:09:27.697 --> 00:09:28.655
Come on.

199
00:09:28.698 --> 00:09:31.527
Easy.

200
00:09:31.571 --> 00:09:34.182
Come on.

201
00:09:34.225 --> 00:09:35.966
That smell--

202
00:09:36.010 --> 00:09:38.142
I love it.

203
00:09:38.186 --> 00:09:39.840
Maybe you and I aren't
picking up on the same scent.

204
00:09:39.883 --> 00:09:42.364
Oh. it takes me back. My foster
mother liked to play the horses.

205
00:09:42.407 --> 00:09:44.627
and she used to take me with her
to the track every Sunday.

206
00:09:44.671 --> 00:09:46.586
Doesn't sound like
an appropriate place

207
00:09:46.629 --> 00:09:48.196
to bring a kid.
No. I loved it.

208
00:09:48.239 --> 00:09:49.806
The-the beautiful horses.

209
00:09:49.850 --> 00:09:52.243
the exciting races.
the betting strategy.

210
00:09:52.287 --> 00:09:55.595
Look. not to brag.
but I know how to pick a winner.

211
00:09:55.638 --> 00:09:56.683
Well. that's probably why
she kept bringing you then.

212
00:09:56.726 --> 00:09:58.119
Oh. totally.
I helped

213
00:09:58.162 --> 00:09:59.642
that woman pay off her house.

214
00:09:59.686 --> 00:10:01.165
Nice. huh?
If you like space.

215
00:10:02.471 --> 00:10:04.038
It belongs to Garrett Sinclair.

216
00:10:04.081 --> 00:10:05.953
His family's been raising
and training horses here

217
00:10:05.996 --> 00:10:08.216
at Bridleright Farms
for generations.

218
00:10:08.259 --> 00:10:10.740
Local fire department finished
their investigation yet?

219
00:10:10.784 --> 00:10:12.437
Got the preliminary report
this morning.

220
00:10:12.481 --> 00:10:13.917
There's no definitive proof
it was arson.

221
00:10:13.961 --> 00:10:15.963
Great. What's our expert say?

222
00:10:16.006 --> 00:10:18.269
Anything we can point to
to say this was an accident?

223
00:10:18.313 --> 00:10:20.358
He's just finishing up.
We should head over...

224
00:10:20.402 --> 00:10:22.360
Can I help you?

225
00:10:22.404 --> 00:10:24.188
Uh. you two go ahead.
I've got this.

226
00:10:35.722 --> 00:10:37.985
Mind telling me who you are
and what you're doing here?

227
00:10:38.028 --> 00:10:39.813
My name is Marissa Morgan.

228
00:10:39.856 --> 00:10:41.815
I work with the legal team
representing Rafael Ramirez.

229
00:10:44.034 --> 00:10:46.602
This is my property.
You need to leave.

230
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:49.083
We will get out of your hair
as quickly as possible.

231
00:10:49.126 --> 00:10:50.824
I know this must be a very
difficult time for you.

232
00:10:50.867 --> 00:10:52.695
Ugh. Difficult's
an understatement.

233
00:10:52.739 --> 00:10:54.436
Lauren Parker was a good friend.

234
00:10:54.479 --> 00:10:57.657
And Bold Spirit was... oh.

235
00:10:58.701 --> 00:11:00.703
Bold Spirit was quite a horse.

236
00:11:00.747 --> 00:11:02.662
At the Breeders' Cup last year.

237
00:11:02.705 --> 00:11:04.402
he ran like he was shot
out of a cannon.

238
00:11:05.403 --> 00:11:07.362
You follow racing?

239
00:11:07.405 --> 00:11:08.798
Here and there.

240
00:11:08.842 --> 00:11:10.321
Then you know.

241
00:11:10.365 --> 00:11:13.629
Bold Spirit was
the kind of horse that...

242
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:15.849
only comes along
once in a lifetime.

243
00:11:17.154 --> 00:11:19.809
Mind if I ask.
these tracks--

244
00:11:19.853 --> 00:11:21.071
are they from Rafael's truck?

245
00:11:21.115 --> 00:11:23.073
Yes.

246
00:11:23.117 --> 00:11:25.728
Looks like he was driving
towards your house.

247
00:11:26.773 --> 00:11:28.209
And your point is?

248
00:11:28.252 --> 00:11:29.732
It seems to me. if Rafael
had set the fire.

249
00:11:29.776 --> 00:11:30.907
he would have been driving
towards the exit.

250
00:11:30.951 --> 00:11:32.343
not towards your house.

251
00:11:32.387 --> 00:11:34.258
Ms. Morgan. do you have any idea

252
00:11:34.302 --> 00:11:35.651
how drunk
Rafael was that night?

253
00:11:35.695 --> 00:11:37.479
I understand he was inebriated.

254
00:11:37.522 --> 00:11:39.220
He was barely conscious.

255
00:11:39.263 --> 00:11:40.743
I doubt he had any idea

256
00:11:40.787 --> 00:11:42.136
where he was driving.

257
00:11:42.179 --> 00:11:43.833
Being an addict

258
00:11:43.877 --> 00:11:45.748
and being an arsonist
aren't the same thing.

259
00:11:45.792 --> 00:11:50.100
Listen. I've sat where you are
now. wanting to believe him.

260
00:11:50.144 --> 00:11:52.494
But this isn't the first time
Rafael has screwed up.

261
00:11:52.537 --> 00:11:54.844
Screwed up how?
I've bailed him out of trouble

262
00:11:54.888 --> 00:11:58.065
because of his drinking
more than once.

263
00:11:59.327 --> 00:12:00.894
I wanted to help.

264
00:12:00.937 --> 00:12:02.765
Look what that got me.

265
00:12:05.333 --> 00:12:07.378
As soon
as your work is finished.

266
00:12:07.422 --> 00:12:09.816
I'd appreciate you
seeing yourself off my farm.

267
00:12:14.385 --> 00:12:16.344
Well. that looked
unpleasant.

268
00:12:16.387 --> 00:12:18.520
The man lost a lot.

269
00:12:18.563 --> 00:12:20.696
Any love from our expert?

270
00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:23.133
Another inconclusive. Nothing
to say it was an accident.

271
00:12:23.177 --> 00:12:24.918
and nothing to say it wasn't.

272
00:12:24.961 --> 00:12:26.833
All I hear is. the
prosecution doesn't have

273
00:12:26.876 --> 00:12:28.922
any direct evidence
that this was arson.

274
00:12:28.965 --> 00:12:31.185
That's something
I can work with.

275
00:12:31.228 --> 00:12:33.535
That is something.
but we may have another problem.

276
00:12:33.578 --> 00:12:36.190
According to Mr. Sinclair.
this is not the first time

277
00:12:36.233 --> 00:12:38.758
that Rafael's drinking
has gotten him in trouble.

278
00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:42.805
Your Honor. Mr. Ramirez's
previous conduct

279
00:12:42.849 --> 00:12:45.939
is clearly inadmissible under
the prior bad acts exclusion.

280
00:12:45.982 --> 00:12:47.767
There are many exceptions
to that rule.

281
00:12:47.810 --> 00:12:49.290
None of which apply here.

282
00:12:49.333 --> 00:12:51.814
The prosecutor is saying
that because my client

283
00:12:51.858 --> 00:12:53.207
got drunk and broke
the law before.

284
00:12:53.250 --> 00:12:55.296
that he must have
done it again here now.

285
00:12:55.339 --> 00:12:56.863
It is the very definition

286
00:12:56.906 --> 00:12:58.212
of inadmissible
character evidence.

287
00:12:58.255 --> 00:13:00.083
On two separate occasions.

288
00:13:00.127 --> 00:13:03.217
the defendant assaulted someone
while intoxicated.

289
00:13:03.260 --> 00:13:05.915
This pattern of vengeful
behavior is highly probative

290
00:13:05.959 --> 00:13:07.961
to the issue of intent.
Your Honor.

291
00:13:08.004 --> 00:13:10.006
Two bar fights do not equate

292
00:13:10.050 --> 00:13:11.965
to intentionally
setting a barn on fire

293
00:13:12.008 --> 00:13:13.923
and killing a person
and a horse.

294
00:13:13.967 --> 00:13:15.359
Your Honor. these incidents

295
00:13:15.403 --> 00:13:16.752
show an escalation that's...

296
00:13:16.796 --> 00:13:17.840
Hold on. Ms. Martin.

297
00:13:17.884 --> 00:13:21.409
Are we boring you. Mr. Ramirez?

298
00:13:23.193 --> 00:13:27.241
Mr. Ramirez.
I'm talking to you.

299
00:13:27.284 --> 00:13:29.634
Oh. my client is-is merely
nervous. Your Honor.

300
00:13:29.678 --> 00:13:30.810
He meant no disrespect.

301
00:13:30.853 --> 00:13:32.812
Does your client speak?

302
00:13:34.291 --> 00:13:36.337
Uh. I'm sorry. Your Honor.

303
00:13:36.380 --> 00:13:39.035
I'm just nervous.
like Mr. Palmer said.

304
00:13:44.998 --> 00:13:48.610
I believe these prior acts
are probative as to intent.

305
00:13:48.653 --> 00:13:50.133
I will allow them.

306
00:13:50.177 --> 00:13:52.266
Thank you. Your Honor.
Mr. Ramirez.

307
00:13:52.309 --> 00:13:54.485
you stand accused
of a very serious crime.

308
00:13:54.529 --> 00:13:57.010
You might want
to pay more attention.

309
00:13:59.229 --> 00:14:01.710
Mr. Ramirez? Mr. Ramirez?

310
00:14:01.753 --> 00:14:04.365
That judge might as well
have called him "Señor."

311
00:14:04.408 --> 00:14:05.888
Izzy. it was odd. absolutely.

312
00:14:05.932 --> 00:14:07.368
but you have
to understand...No. no.

313
00:14:07.411 --> 00:14:08.848
My Tía Rosa
with her collection

314
00:14:08.891 --> 00:14:10.458
of porcelain
cat figurines is odd.

315
00:14:10.501 --> 00:14:13.069
This was outrageous.

316
00:14:13.113 --> 00:14:14.636
He's racist.

317
00:14:14.679 --> 00:14:16.768
We don't know that.
Oh. I do.

318
00:14:18.118 --> 00:14:19.815
That judge is biased
against Raf.

319
00:14:19.859 --> 00:14:20.947
and you have
to get him off the case.

320
00:14:20.990 --> 00:14:22.862
Just like that? Remove a judge?

321
00:14:22.905 --> 00:14:24.689
Well. Raf is never gonna get

322
00:14:24.733 --> 00:14:26.909
a fair trial with that jerk.
and you know it.

323
00:14:26.953 --> 00:14:28.302
Well. it is
incredibly difficult

324
00:14:28.345 --> 00:14:29.825
to get a judge
kicked off for prejudice.

325
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:31.522
Well. so? We got to try.

326
00:14:31.566 --> 00:14:33.698
I'm the only person that's ever
been in Raf's corner.

327
00:14:33.742 --> 00:14:35.309
and I'm not going down
without a fight.

328
00:14:37.485 --> 00:14:39.269
I get that. but...

329
00:14:40.531 --> 00:14:44.622
I said. I get that.
but if we make the accusation.

330
00:14:44.666 --> 00:14:46.624
and we don't succeed
in getting Judge Grant removed.

331
00:14:46.668 --> 00:14:48.452
we still have to try the case.

332
00:14:48.496 --> 00:14:50.541
except this time with a judge
who's very pissed off with us.

333
00:14:50.585 --> 00:14:52.587
So there's nothing we could do?

334
00:14:52.630 --> 00:14:55.068
Well. Taylor is looking into
Judge Grant's previous rulings

335
00:14:55.111 --> 00:14:57.070
to see if there's a pattern
of prejudice.

336
00:14:57.113 --> 00:14:59.550
especially
against Latinx defendants.

337
00:14:59.594 --> 00:15:00.987
but it's gonna take some time.

338
00:15:01.030 --> 00:15:02.989
Okay. and until then?

339
00:15:03.032 --> 00:15:05.556
We start telling our story.

340
00:15:05.600 --> 00:15:08.081
What happened to Lauren Parker

341
00:15:08.124 --> 00:15:11.040
and Bold Spirit
was undoubtedly tragic.

342
00:15:11.084 --> 00:15:13.695
It was also
a tragic accident.

343
00:15:13.738 --> 00:15:15.436
You won't hear any evidence

344
00:15:15.479 --> 00:15:19.440
proving that this fire started
as a result of arson

345
00:15:19.483 --> 00:15:21.529
because the prosecution
doesn't have any.

346
00:15:21.572 --> 00:15:22.965
And you'll hear no evidence

347
00:15:23.009 --> 00:15:25.098
whatsoever that Mr. Ramirez

348
00:15:25.141 --> 00:15:29.537
started that fire
because... he didn't.

349
00:15:29.580 --> 00:15:30.973
How's Chunk doing?

350
00:15:31.017 --> 00:15:32.757
Uh. it's a strong
opening argument.

351
00:15:35.847 --> 00:15:37.371
You waiting for something?

352
00:15:37.414 --> 00:15:40.330
I texted Henri again
this morning.

353
00:15:40.374 --> 00:15:42.332
I was just hoping...

354
00:15:42.376 --> 00:15:44.378
He still hasn't
talked to you?

355
00:15:44.421 --> 00:15:47.381
No. not since... you know.

356
00:15:47.424 --> 00:15:49.383
I'm so sorry.
I feel so responsible.

357
00:15:49.426 --> 00:15:51.472
What's done is done.
You and I are good.

358
00:15:51.515 --> 00:15:53.691
I just...

359
00:15:53.735 --> 00:15:55.998
I hate that he thinks
so poorly of me.

360
00:15:56.042 --> 00:15:58.522
I didn't even get
to explain myself.

361
00:15:58.566 --> 00:16:00.002
So explain yourself.

362
00:16:00.046 --> 00:16:02.918
How? He's not responding to me.
Come on.

363
00:16:02.962 --> 00:16:04.528
You figured out a way
to make Bull listen to you.

364
00:16:04.572 --> 00:16:06.356
and now you're a partner in TAC.

365
00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.054
Think you can figure out a way
to get through to Henri.

366
00:16:09.272 --> 00:16:11.492
Oh.

367
00:16:11.535 --> 00:16:13.320
Hey. Danny. What's up?

368
00:16:14.321 --> 00:16:16.845
Oh. no.

369
00:16:16.888 --> 00:16:20.849
Lauren Parker was Mr. Ramirez's
colleague and friend.

370
00:16:20.892 --> 00:16:24.331
And Bold Spirit was his partner.
He had absolutely

371
00:16:24.374 --> 00:16:27.595
no motive
to harm either one of them.

372
00:16:27.638 --> 00:16:28.944
Bull. uh.

373
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:29.771
you need to go out in the hall.

374
00:16:29.814 --> 00:16:31.512
Talk to Danny.

375
00:16:31.555 --> 00:16:33.470
Chunk hasn't finished
his opening statements.

376
00:16:33.514 --> 00:16:34.776
Go now.

377
00:16:34.819 --> 00:16:36.169
He never would have

378
00:16:36.212 --> 00:16:38.736
