Why am I such a screwup?
Calm down.

421
00:18:21.143 --> 00:18:22.492
Hey. hey!

422
00:18:22.536 --> 00:18:24.668
Look at me.

423
00:18:24.712 --> 00:18:27.454
You need to keep it together.
especially when we're in court.

424
00:18:30.718 --> 00:18:33.460
You never wanted
a drink that bad?

425
00:18:33.503 --> 00:18:35.940
Yeah.

426
00:18:35.984 --> 00:18:39.770
I know moments of weakness
can trigger negative actions.

427
00:18:40.771 --> 00:18:42.121
Yeah.

428
00:18:42.164 --> 00:18:43.644
You got to stay sober.

429
00:18:43.687 --> 00:18:44.819
When was the last time
you went to a meeting?

430
00:18:44.862 --> 00:18:47.691
Has it been a long time?

431
00:18:47.735 --> 00:18:49.563
A while.
Okay.

432
00:18:49.606 --> 00:18:52.914
Most important thing in
your life right now is sobriety.

433
00:18:52.957 --> 00:18:55.960
So after court. you go?

434
00:18:56.004 --> 00:18:58.311
I will.

435
00:18:58.354 --> 00:18:59.660
Good.

436
00:18:59.703 --> 00:19:01.357
I made a promise to Izzy.

437
00:19:01.401 --> 00:19:05.709
Oh. Well. then. yeah.
in that case.

438
00:19:05.753 --> 00:19:07.146
God help you
if you don't keep it.

439
00:19:14.718 --> 00:19:16.764
I'm sorry. but Operation
Judgy Judge was a bust.

440
00:19:16.807 --> 00:19:18.200
Operation Judgy Judge?

441
00:19:18.244 --> 00:19:19.941
My deep dive into Judge Grant.

442
00:19:19.984 --> 00:19:21.986
I checked his sentencing history
of Latino

443
00:19:22.030 --> 00:19:24.511
versus non-Latino defendants
and found no evidence

444
00:19:24.554 --> 00:19:25.512
of racial bias.
None at all?

445
00:19:25.555 --> 00:19:26.991
In fact. he's slightly

446
00:19:27.035 --> 00:19:28.167
more lenient towards Latinos.

447
00:19:29.385 --> 00:19:31.474
I would've bet money
that he was biased

448
00:19:31.518 --> 00:19:33.128
based on how he talked
to Rafael.

449
00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:35.957
Maybe Rafael reminds him
of someone from his past.

450
00:19:36.000 --> 00:19:37.524
I can look into that.

451
00:19:37.567 --> 00:19:39.178
No. I don't want to send you
on a wild goose chase.

452
00:19:39.221 --> 00:19:40.614
Sometimes you get a bad ref.

453
00:19:40.657 --> 00:19:42.355
You still have to play to win.

454
00:19:42.398 --> 00:19:43.834
I think our best move is
to find someone else

455
00:19:43.878 --> 00:19:45.532
who had motive
to burn down that barn.

456
00:19:45.575 --> 00:19:47.098
Oh. I already did that.

457
00:19:47.142 --> 00:19:49.840
What?

458
00:19:49.884 --> 00:19:50.972
What'd you find?

459
00:19:54.193 --> 00:19:56.325
Rafael said
I'd regret firing him.

460
00:19:56.369 --> 00:19:58.066
He wanted to hurt me.

461
00:19:58.109 --> 00:20:00.460
Setting that fire.
killing Bold Spirit.

462
00:20:00.503 --> 00:20:03.158
was his way of doing that.
I don't know if he even

463
00:20:03.202 --> 00:20:05.334
realized Lauren was in the barn.

464
00:20:08.424 --> 00:20:12.254
It's still hard for me
to believe she's gone. too.

465
00:20:12.298 --> 00:20:14.343
Thank you. Mr. Sinclair.

466
00:20:14.387 --> 00:20:15.866
Nothing further. Your Honor.

467
00:20:15.910 --> 00:20:17.128
Your witness. Mr. Palmer.

468
00:20:18.695 --> 00:20:20.654
Mr. Sinclair.

469
00:20:20.697 --> 00:20:23.222
six months ago.
another one of your horses.

470
00:20:23.265 --> 00:20:25.963
Gold Rush. died prematurely.
is that correct?

471
00:20:26.007 --> 00:20:27.356
Um. yes.

472
00:20:27.400 --> 00:20:30.098
Actually.
he was my husband's horse.

473
00:20:30.141 --> 00:20:32.753
I got Gold Rush for Noah
when he retired

474
00:20:32.796 --> 00:20:35.146
from his veterinary
practice. We were

475
00:20:35.190 --> 00:20:37.888
both devastated by his loss.

476
00:20:37.932 --> 00:20:41.196
And did you file an insurance
claim upon Gold Rush's death?

477
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:43.807
Yes. It might seem strange

478
00:20:43.851 --> 00:20:47.463
to insure a pet.
but Gold Rush

479
00:20:47.507 --> 00:20:49.422
wasn't just a pet.
He was a thoroughbred racehorse.

480
00:20:49.465 --> 00:20:51.119
Very expensive.

481
00:20:51.162 --> 00:20:55.689
And what was the payout
from Gold Rush's policy?

482
00:20:55.732 --> 00:20:57.778
$1 million. but

483
00:20:57.821 --> 00:20:58.996
no amount of money could

484
00:20:59.040 --> 00:21:01.172
replace him in Noah's heart.

485
00:21:01.216 --> 00:21:03.610
Noah was crazy about that horse.

486
00:21:03.653 --> 00:21:05.220
Whose side are you on?

487
00:21:05.264 --> 00:21:06.221
What about Bold Spirit?

488
00:21:06.265 --> 00:21:07.222
Champion racer.

489
00:21:07.266 --> 00:21:08.484
You must have taken out

490
00:21:08.528 --> 00:21:10.399
a much bigger policy for him.

491
00:21:10.443 --> 00:21:12.662
Objection.
Leading the witness.
I'll rephrase.

492
00:21:12.706 --> 00:21:14.098
Please do.

493
00:21:14.142 --> 00:21:16.666
What's the insurance payout
going

494
00:21:16.710 --> 00:21:18.451
to be for Bold Spirit?

495
00:21:18.494 --> 00:21:20.104
$5 million.

496
00:21:21.454 --> 00:21:23.499
But that doesn't

497
00:21:23.543 --> 00:21:25.893
even begin to cover
what we would have earned

498
00:21:25.936 --> 00:21:27.416
had he kept racing.

499
00:21:27.460 --> 00:21:29.288
You mean.
had he kept winning. right?

500
00:21:29.331 --> 00:21:31.246
Bold Spirit
won the last

501
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:34.031
seven of his stakes races.

502
00:21:34.075 --> 00:21:36.425
People were talking about his
chances at the Triple Crown.

503
00:21:36.469 --> 00:21:38.297
Sure.
but a winning streak can end

504
00:21:38.340 --> 00:21:39.950
just as quickly as it began.

505
00:21:39.994 --> 00:21:42.518
Perhaps you were trying
to guarantee a windfall.

506
00:21:42.562 --> 00:21:43.954
and so you killed the horse
yourself.

507
00:21:43.998 --> 00:21:46.914
Objection. Your Honor.
Counsel is testifying.

508
00:21:46.957 --> 00:21:49.090
He sure is. I object. too.

509
00:21:49.133 --> 00:21:50.265
You object?

510
00:21:50.309 --> 00:21:51.962
Excuse me. Your Honor?

511
00:21:52.006 --> 00:21:54.400
I've let your fishing expedition
go on long enough.

512
00:21:54.443 --> 00:21:56.271
Your cross is over. Mr. Palmer.

513
00:21:56.315 --> 00:21:58.317
Due respect of the court.
Your Honor. but I'm not finished

514
00:21:58.360 --> 00:22:00.101
with Mr. Sinclair.
Yes. you are.

515
00:22:00.144 --> 00:22:02.321
Your Honor. you cannot
deny me the opportunity

516
00:22:02.364 --> 00:22:04.279
to cross-examine
a prosecution witness.

517
00:22:04.323 --> 00:22:07.500
I can. and I did.
Take a seat.

518
00:22:08.762 --> 00:22:10.067
No.

519
00:22:10.111 --> 00:22:11.547
Not until

520
00:22:11.591 --> 00:22:12.983
I'm finished.

521
00:22:13.027 --> 00:22:14.463
This witness is excused.

522
00:22:14.507 --> 00:22:17.727
Counsel in my chambers. Now.

523
00:22:25.213 --> 00:22:26.475
What's the problem?

524
00:22:26.519 --> 00:22:28.172
Well. I guess
Rafael isn't the only one

525
00:22:28.216 --> 00:22:30.305
the judge has it
in for now.

526
00:22:33.221 --> 00:22:34.744
Mr. Palmer.

527
00:22:34.788 --> 00:22:37.965
your treatment
of that witness was repugnant.

528
00:22:38.008 --> 00:22:40.750
Garrett Sinclair
is the victim here.

529
00:22:40.794 --> 00:22:42.578
Garrett Sinclair is a witness
and a possible suspect.

530
00:22:42.622 --> 00:22:45.494
Mr. Sinclair didn't just lose

531
00:22:45.538 --> 00:22:47.714
his employee.
He lost his beloved horse.

532
00:22:47.757 --> 00:22:49.498
I won't have you badgering him
in my courtroom.

533
00:22:49.542 --> 00:22:50.978
Your Honor.

534
00:22:51.021 --> 00:22:54.024
respectfully.
Lauren Parker and Bold Spirit

535
00:22:54.068 --> 00:22:57.419
are the only two victims
in this entire case.

536
00:22:57.463 --> 00:23:00.335
That man is in mourning.
Don't you have any compassion?

537
00:23:00.379 --> 00:23:02.119
I have compassion
for my client

538
00:23:02.163 --> 00:23:03.686
who's been wrongfully accused

539
00:23:03.730 --> 00:23:05.384
and deserves the best defense
that I can give him.

540
00:23:05.427 --> 00:23:08.691
I can't even imagine
how devastated I'd be

541
00:23:08.735 --> 00:23:10.389
if anything like that happened
to my Lucy.

542
00:23:10.432 --> 00:23:12.782
If I'm not allowed to continue
my cross-examination.

543
00:23:12.826 --> 00:23:15.437
I'm going to file an immediate
interlocutory appeal!

544
00:23:15.481 --> 00:23:16.830
We're not gonna do that.

545
00:23:16.873 --> 00:23:18.701
And I want
to apologize profusely

546
00:23:18.745 --> 00:23:20.442
for our insensitivity here.

547
00:23:20.486 --> 00:23:21.617
It will never
happen again.

548
00:23:21.661 --> 00:23:23.619
Your Honor.
Mr. Palmer. shall we?

549
00:23:29.843 --> 00:23:32.628
What the hell was that? You just
cut me off at the knees.

550
00:23:32.672 --> 00:23:35.152
Did you see his dog?
What?

551
00:23:35.196 --> 00:23:38.286
Lucy? Judge Grant's dog.

552
00:23:38.329 --> 00:23:39.809
The man's an animal lover.

553
00:23:39.853 --> 00:23:42.377
And he thinks
that Rafael killed a horse.

554
00:23:42.421 --> 00:23:43.770
That's why he's being
so hard on him.

555
00:23:43.813 --> 00:23:46.468
He thinks it's worse
to kill an animal than a person?

556
00:23:46.512 --> 00:23:48.209
I don't know
if he thinks it's worse.

557
00:23:48.252 --> 00:23:50.472
but the man's got
a soft spot. He's...

558
00:23:50.516 --> 00:23:54.607
polluting the jury right now
with his contempt for Rafael.

559
00:23:54.650 --> 00:23:58.654
If we want to win them over.
we need to win him over first.

560
00:23:58.698 --> 00:24:00.439
Shall I go back in there
and sweet-talk him some more?

561
00:24:00.482 --> 00:24:03.442
No. we got to put Rafael on
the stand. and he has to testify

562
00:24:03.485 --> 00:24:06.009
about how much he loves horses.

563
00:24:06.053 --> 00:24:07.837
And the judge will never believe

564
00:24:07.881 --> 00:24:09.578
that he would burn down a barn
with a horse in it.

565
00:24:09.622 --> 00:24:12.494
Rafael's fragile. You think
he's gonna hold up on cross?

566
00:24:12.538 --> 00:24:14.104
Better than he's gonna hold up
in prison.

567
00:24:21.068 --> 00:24:22.983
Forgive me. but
we're closing.

568
00:24:24.463 --> 00:24:27.074
I promise I won't keep you long.

569
00:24:27.117 --> 00:24:29.032
Marissa.
what are you doing here?

570
00:24:29.076 --> 00:24:31.034
You said the reason
you didn't tell me

571
00:24:31.078 --> 00:24:33.036
you were still married
is because

572
00:24:33.080 --> 00:24:36.910
you didn't want to burden a new
relationship with old wounds.

573
00:24:36.953 --> 00:24:40.087
And the irony is
that I burdened our relationship

574
00:24:40.130 --> 00:24:41.262
with my old wounds.

575
00:24:41.305 --> 00:24:43.307
I-I'm not sure I understand.

576
00:24:43.351 --> 00:24:46.223
I consider myself
to be a smart woman.

577
00:24:46.267 --> 00:24:48.835
but I have been deceived

578
00:24:48.878 --> 00:24:50.880
by men quite a few times.

579
00:24:50.924 --> 00:24:53.492
Well. we've all been lied to
at some point.

580
00:24:53.535 --> 00:24:55.755
A con man stole all of my money.

581
00:24:55.798 --> 00:24:58.845
My ex-husband nearly got me
sent to prison for his crimes.

582
00:24:58.888 --> 00:25:00.281
And that was
after I divorced him

583
00:25:00.324 --> 00:25:03.327
and married him
for a second time.

584
00:25:04.372 --> 00:25:07.288
I'm sorry that happened to you.

585
00:25:07.331 --> 00:25:11.945
My point is
that all of this has left me

586
00:25:11.988 --> 00:25:16.471
a little wary of things
that seem too good to be true.

587
00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:19.213
That's why
I investigated you.

588
00:25:19.256 --> 00:25:21.215
I see.

589
00:25:21.258 --> 00:25:22.651
It wasn't fair for me

590
00:25:22.695 --> 00:25:26.046
to project my past onto you.

591
00:25:26.089 --> 00:25:28.091
So...

592
00:25:28.135 --> 00:25:30.311
please forgive me.

593
00:25:31.747 --> 00:25:33.532
Henri...

594
00:25:34.968 --> 00:25:36.665
Um...

595
00:25:36.709 --> 00:25:37.753
Oh.

596
00:25:39.929 --> 00:25:41.148
You're busy.

597
00:25:41.191 --> 00:25:42.410
Marissa...Uh.

598
00:25:42.453 --> 00:25:45.108
I'm interrupting.
and I'm gonna go.

599
00:25:50.853 --> 00:25:52.159
Okay.

600
00:25:57.643 --> 00:25:59.601
Horses saved my life.

601
00:25:59.645 --> 00:26:01.603
Can you please tell
the court what you mean

602
00:26:01.647 --> 00:26:03.213
when you say
they saved your life?

603
00:26:03.257 --> 00:26:05.346
I moved to this country
from Puerto Rico

604
00:26:05.389 --> 00:26:06.695
when I was 12 years old.

605
00:26:06.739 --> 00:26:09.350
I didn't speak
the same language

606
00:26:09.393 --> 00:26:11.439
as the other kids
at school. didn't

607
00:26:11.482 --> 00:26:13.789
have any friends.
Home wasn't any easier.

608
00:26:13.833 --> 00:26:15.748
My father was abusive.

609
00:26:15.791 --> 00:26:17.924
Well. that sounds like
a lot for a boy to carry.

610
00:26:17.967 --> 00:26:20.013
How did horses come
into your life?

611
00:26:20.056 --> 00:26:23.582
I-I got assigned a mentor at the
Puerto Rican Community Center.

612
00:26:23.625 --> 00:26:26.193
My mentor-- she did
all sorts of things with me.

613
00:26:26.236 --> 00:26:29.588
One day. she took me to
these stables for a trail ride.

614
00:26:29.631 --> 00:26:33.374
Horses-- they don't care
what country you come from.

615
00:26:33.417 --> 00:26:37.117
what language you speak.
or even if your dad hits you.

616
00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:39.641
They just need you to
love and care for them.

617
00:26:39.685 --> 00:26:42.426
And when you do.
they love you in return.

618
00:26:42.470 --> 00:26:46.213
And this love
you have for horses--

619
00:26:46.256 --> 00:26:48.781
it led to a career
with them. right?

620
00:26:48.824 --> 00:26:50.609
Yes.

621
00:26:50.652 --> 00:26:52.219
I mucked the stalls and

622
00:26:52.262 --> 00:26:55.222
groomed the horses
in exchange for riding lessons.

623
00:26:55.265 --> 00:26:57.441
It came pretty naturally to me.

624
00:26:57.485 --> 00:26:59.922
and. uh. the owner
of the stables-- he noticed.

625
00:26:59.966 --> 00:27:02.621
He sponsored my training
to become a jockey.

626
00:27:02.664 --> 00:27:04.840
I never could've
dreamed I'd spend

627
00:27:04.884 --> 00:27:06.842
my life working with horses.

628
00:27:06.886 --> 00:27:08.278
He's doing well.

629
00:27:08.322 --> 00:27:09.715
Extremely well.

630
00:27:09.758 --> 00:27:11.630
Mr. Ramirez.

631
00:27:11.673 --> 00:27:14.241
did you set the fire
that killed Lauren Parker

632
00:27:14.284 --> 00:27:15.677
and Bold Spirit?

633
00:27:15.721 --> 00:27:17.766
No.

634
00:27:17.810 --> 00:27:19.289
No. Lauren was my friend.

635
00:27:19.333 --> 00:27:20.769
And she was always
very good to me.

636
00:27:20.813 --> 00:27:22.728
Bold Spirit was my partner.

637
00:27:22.771 --> 00:27:24.773
I loved him.

638
00:27:27.820 --> 00:27:29.604
I can't believe
that they're gone.

639
00:27:31.345 --> 00:27:33.216
And I couldn't live with myself

640
00:27:33.260 --> 00:27:34.609
if I had been the one
who killed them.

641
00:27:34.653 --> 00:27:36.829
Thank you. Mr. Ramirez.

642
00:27:36.872 --> 00:27:38.787
No further questions.
Your Honor.

643
00:27:39.788 --> 00:27:41.224
Let's. uh.

644
00:27:41.268 --> 00:27:43.879
take a brief recess
for lunch and

645
00:27:43.923 --> 00:27:45.576
pick up with Ms. Martin's
cross-examination

646
00:27:45.620 --> 00:27:47.709
when we return.

647
00:28:00.766 --> 00:28:04.770
Hey. we need to talk
to Rafael. Now.

648
00:28:12.821 --> 00:28:15.302
Let me see that bottle.
What? Why?

649
00:28:15.345 --> 00:28:16.085
Have you been drinking?

650
00:28:16.129 --> 00:28:17.957
No.

651
00:28:18.000 --> 00:28:19.698
Let me see the bottle.
Hey... it's just water.

652
00:28:21.482 --> 00:28:22.918
Vodka.

653
00:28:23.919 --> 00:28:25.355
Look. it was only

654
00:28:25.399 --> 00:28:27.140
a few sips to calm my nerves.
you know?

655
00:28:27.183 --> 00:28:28.750
It's not like
I'm drunk or anything.

656
00:28:28.794 --> 00:28:31.057
Bull. can I speak
to you for a second?

657
00:28:33.320 --> 00:28:35.235
You stay here.

658
00:28:39.108 --> 00:28:41.371
We can't put him back
on the stand today.
Agreed.

659
00:28:41.415 --> 00:28:43.286
Ask for a recess until tomorrow.

660
00:28:43.330 --> 00:28:46.159
On what grounds?
Well. I don't know.

661
00:28:46.202 --> 00:28:47.421
Tell the judge he ate
a bad shrimp or something.

662
00:28:47.464 --> 00:28:49.466
We can't lie to a judge.

663
00:28:49.510 --> 00:28:51.294
We don't know it's a lie.
He could have had a bad shrimp.

664
00:28:51.338 --> 00:28:54.341
It's a lie. and if Rafael
was drinking on the stand.

665
00:28:54.384 --> 00:28:55.951
I'm obligated
to inform the judge

666
00:28:55.995 --> 00:28:57.605
that his testimony's unreliable.

667
00:28:57.648 --> 00:28:59.607
Unreliable? Now wait a second.

668
00:28:59.650 --> 00:29:00.826
We have no reason to believe

669
00:29:00.869 --> 00:29:02.305
that Rafael wasn't
telling the truth.

670
00:29:02.349 --> 00:29:03.959
He did not
perjure himself.

671
00:29:04.003 --> 00:29:06.962
I'm an officer of the court.
and I have a duty. Bull.

672
00:29:07.006 --> 00:29:08.877
What about your duty to Rafael?

673
00:29:08.921 --> 00:29:12.402
When this jury finds out
that he was drunk on the stand.

674
00:29:12.446 --> 00:29:16.189
they're gonna hate him. and you
will have jeopardized this case.

675
00:29:16.232 --> 00:29:17.973
Rafael jeopardized his own case.

676
00:29:18.017 --> 00:29:21.411
You want to lie to a judge.
that's fine.

677
00:29:21.455 --> 00:29:23.936
but you'll have to find
another attorney to do it.

678
00:29:36.992 --> 00:29:39.342
In light
of Mr. Palmer's disclosure

679
00:29:39.386 --> 00:29:41.388
regarding his client's
intoxication.

680
00:29:41.431 --> 00:29:43.782
I must ask you.
members of the jury.

681
00:29:43.825 --> 00:29:45.653
to disregard

682
00:29:45.696 --> 00:29:48.961
the testimony
we just heard from Mr. Ramirez.

683
00:29:50.701 --> 00:29:53.530
Help me understand how
you can do this to yourself.

684
00:29:53.574 --> 00:29:55.532
I'm sorry. Izzy. I...

685
00:29:55.576 --> 00:29:57.926
You have all these people
here to help you.

686
00:29:57.970 --> 00:29:59.580
I'm here to help.

687
00:29:59.623 --> 00:30:00.407
Why can't you help yourself?

688
00:30:00.450 --> 00:30:02.888
I-I don't know.

689
00:30:04.193 --> 00:30:06.979
This is your life
on the line. Raf.

690
00:30:07.022 --> 00:30:08.632
It's the only one you got.
I-I know.

691
00:30:08.676 --> 00:30:10.809
I. I-I know.

692
00:30:10.852 --> 00:30:13.376
Do you remember what I told you
the first time we met?

693
00:30:13.420 --> 00:30:14.595
Yeah. of course.

694
00:30:14.638 --> 00:30:16.684
Tú eres un rey. Rafael.

695
00:30:17.903 --> 00:30:20.035
Vaya con la cabeza bien alta.

696
00:30:20.079 --> 00:30:22.603
You are a king.

697
00:30:22.646 --> 00:30:24.648
Now go with your head held high.

698
00:30:28.914 --> 00:30:31.873
Well. we tried it
your way. Now what?

699
00:30:31.917 --> 00:30:34.354
I don't know.
I'll come up with something.

700
00:30:35.921 --> 00:30:37.357
Make sure he gets
home okay. will you?

701
00:30:37.400 --> 00:30:38.837
Yeah.

702
00:30:40.186 --> 00:30:42.144
How can he show up
to the stand drunk?

703
00:30:42.188 --> 00:30:45.017
I don't understand.
He has so much left to lose.

704
00:30:47.019 --> 00:30:48.977
Well. that is exactly
what happened.

705
00:30:49.021 --> 00:30:50.805
He was under
too much pressure.

706
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:53.808
Drinking is
his coping mechanism.

707
00:30:53.852 --> 00:30:56.637
You know. when I first
met Raf. he was arrested

708
00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:58.639
for shoplifting
a candy at the bodega.

709
00:30:58.682 --> 00:31:01.860
And...
he was so ashamed.

710
00:31:01.903 --> 00:31:05.472
and just seeing that same shame
on his face today just...

711
00:31:05.515 --> 00:31:07.082
it gutted me.

712
00:31:07.126 --> 00:31:12.044
And yet you are
still here by his side.

713
00:31:13.306 --> 00:31:15.264
Is it bad that I really
want a drink right now?

714
00:31:15.308 --> 00:31:17.310
I'm glad you said it first.

715
00:31:20.443 --> 00:31:24.012
Hey. Sorry to hear
about Rafael today.

716
00:31:24.056 --> 00:31:28.060
Yeah. We started out
having a slim chance.

717
00:31:28.103 --> 00:31:30.105
and now we have
a slim chance in hell.

718
00:31:30.149 --> 00:31:31.890
Bull have any ideas
how to spin this?

719
00:31:31.933 --> 00:31:34.240
No. He's passed that
squarely onto me.

720
00:31:34.283 --> 00:31:36.503
So where are you at?
I think our only hope

721
00:31:36.546 --> 00:31:39.332
of winning is by pointing
the finger at someone else.

722
00:31:39.375 --> 00:31:40.681
What? Didn't you already try
to point the finger

723
00:31:40.724 --> 00:31:42.465
at Garrett Sinclair?
Yeah.

724
00:31:42.509 --> 00:31:44.728
You know. he said something
interesting on the stand

725
00:31:44.772 --> 00:31:46.469
that got me thinking.
He said

726
00:31:46.513 --> 00:31:49.472
that Bold Spirit was worth
more alive than he was dead.

727
00:31:49.516 --> 00:31:51.735
And if Bold Spirit is winning
all of these races

728
00:31:51.779 --> 00:31:53.346
and making all of this money.

729
00:31:53.389 --> 00:31:55.522
there's got to be some
sore losers out there. right?

730
00:31:55.565 --> 00:31:56.958
Well. yeah. there are plenty.

731
00:31:57.002 --> 00:31:58.351
Some of them are
especially sore

732
00:31:58.394 --> 00:32:00.483
because they don't think
he won fair and square.

733
00:32:00.527 --> 00:32:02.746
There's a rumor
that Lauren Parker--

734
00:32:02.790 --> 00:32:06.750
the trainer who died in the
fire-- was doping her horses.

735
00:32:06.794 --> 00:32:10.493
Well. if Sinclair's rivals
think that he cheated to win.

736
00:32:10.537 --> 00:32:12.931
robbing them of all of
that money and all that glory.

737
00:32:12.974 --> 00:32:14.454
that's motive right there.

738
00:32:14.497 --> 00:32:16.151
Sure. but it's gonna be hard

739
00:32:16.195 --> 00:32:17.761
to get those old money folks
to testify.

740
00:32:17.805 --> 00:32:18.937
They don't like airing

741
00:32:18.980 --> 00:32:20.590
their dirty laundry.

742
00:32:20.634 --> 00:32:23.115
Well. not to outsiders.
but there is someone

743
00:32:23.158 --> 00:32:26.857
these horse people love
to complain to.

744
00:32:26.901 --> 00:32:28.772
My name is Alex Garves.

745
00:32:28.816 --> 00:32:31.297
I'm the director of the American
Thoroughbred Racing Guild.

746
00:32:31.340 --> 00:32:33.168
And in your position
as director.

747
00:32:33.212 --> 00:32:35.170
do you field complaints

748
00:32:35.214 --> 00:32:37.346
about racehorses being given
performance-enhancing drugs?

749
00:32:37.390 --> 00:32:40.132
I do.
Have you ever received
complaints about

750
00:32:40.175 --> 00:32:42.090
Bold Spirit being doped?

751
00:32:42.134 --> 00:32:44.179
Yes. We've received
a number of allegations

752
00:32:44.223 --> 00:32:45.789
that Bridleright Farms

753
00:32:45.833 --> 00:32:47.313
and their trainer

754
00:32:47.356 --> 00:32:49.010
Lauren Parker

755
00:32:49.054 --> 00:32:51.317
were giving Bold Spirit
performance-enhancing drugs.

756
00:32:51.360 --> 00:32:52.492
And did you investigate
those allegations?

757
00:32:52.535 --> 00:32:54.059
Objection. Your Honor.
Relevance?

758
00:32:54.102 --> 00:32:55.712
Your Honor. the Defense

759
00:32:55.756 --> 00:32:57.105
has the right to present others

760
00:32:57.149 --> 00:32:58.585
with motives
for killing Bold Spirit

761
00:32:58.628 --> 00:33:00.979
and Lauren Parker.

762
00:33:01.022 --> 00:33:02.806
I'll allow it.
We tested

763
00:33:02.850 --> 00:33:04.721
Bold Spirit for the presence
of drugs in his system.

764
00:33:04.765 --> 00:33:06.288
but none was found.

765
00:33:06.332 --> 00:33:08.856
Did that stop the complaints?
No.

766
00:33:08.899 --> 00:33:10.292
The unfortunate reality is

767
00:33:10.336 --> 00:33:12.207
that drug testing
can't keep up

768
00:33:12.251 --> 00:33:14.209
with the availability
of new drugs on the market.

769
00:33:14.253 --> 00:33:16.342
The other owners were certain
that Garrett Sinclair

770
00:33:16.385 --> 00:33:18.344
and his trainer
Lauren Parker were cheating.

771
00:33:18.387 --> 00:33:19.780
but we couldn't prove it.

772
00:33:19.823 --> 00:33:21.173
And did that make

773
00:33:21.216 --> 00:33:24.002
the other owners angry?
Very much so.

774
00:33:24.045 --> 00:33:25.568
There's a lot at stake
in these races.

775
00:33:25.612 --> 00:33:27.092
It's not just bragging rights.

776
00:33:27.135 --> 00:33:29.224
There's millions
in purse winnings. but

777
00:33:29.268 --> 00:33:32.053
the real money's
in stud fees.

778
00:33:32.097 --> 00:33:33.576
Stables can make
over a half million dollars

779
00:33:33.620 --> 00:33:34.751
for a champion's stud fee.

780
00:33:34.795 --> 00:33:36.362
And a horse

781
00:33:36.405 --> 00:33:37.841
can stud almost
a hundred times a year.

782
00:33:37.885 --> 00:33:39.974
Wow. That's a lot of money.

783
00:33:40.018 --> 00:33:42.803
Maybe even enough to kill for.

784
00:33:42.846 --> 00:33:44.370
Thank you. Mr. Garves.

785
00:33:44.413 --> 00:33:47.199
No further questions.
Your Honor.

786
00:33:49.070 --> 00:33:51.159
Chunk made some hay
with the jury.

787
00:33:51.203 --> 00:33:52.856
Yeah. but it looks
like Garrett Sinclair

788
00:33:52.900 --> 00:33:56.251
would like to stick
a pitchfork in his eye.

789
00:33:58.297 --> 00:34:00.995
Bridleright Farms has been
in my family for generations.

790
00:34:01.039 --> 00:34:02.997
I'm proud to uphold
its legacy

791
00:34:03.041 --> 00:34:05.086
of excellence
and also integrity.

792
00:34:05.130 --> 00:34:07.436
Which is why I have not.
nor would I ever.

793
00:34:07.480 --> 00:34:10.613
allow my horses to use
performance-enhancing drugs.

794
00:34:10.657 --> 00:34:13.094
He's laying it on awfully thick.
You think?

795
00:34:13.138 --> 00:34:15.575
I find it unconscionable
that the reputation

796
00:34:15.618 --> 00:34:19.057
of my trusted trainer
Lauren Parker is being attacked

797
00:34:19.100 --> 00:34:21.059
in the wake
of her tragic passing.

798
00:34:21.842 --> 00:34:23.626
You see that?
Hmm. What?

799
00:34:23.670 --> 00:34:25.324
Watch Noah's body language.

800
00:34:25.367 --> 00:34:27.065
Here.

801
00:34:27.108 --> 00:34:28.849
...is being attacked
in the wake

802
00:34:28.892 --> 00:34:30.851
of her tragic passing.

803
00:34:30.894 --> 00:34:32.287
You see how it changed

804
00:34:32.331 --> 00:34:34.202
when Garrett started talking
about Lauren?

805
00:34:34.246 --> 00:34:36.204
He took his hand away.
And crossed his arms.

806
00:34:36.248 --> 00:34:38.032
Classic indicators
of hurt and anger.

807
00:34:38.076 --> 00:34:40.904
Noah doesn't like Lauren.

808
00:34:40.948 --> 00:34:43.472
So what are you saying?

809
00:34:43.516 --> 00:34:45.474
We may have finally
found someone else

810
00:34:45.518 --> 00:34:47.650
who had a motive
to burn down that barn.

811
00:35:03.971 --> 00:35:04.972
Need some help. ma'am?

812
00:35:05.015 --> 00:35:06.713
I do. Thanks for stopping.

813
00:35:06.756 --> 00:35:09.019
I know a thing or two
about cars. Let me take a look.

814
00:35:09.063 --> 00:35:11.413
Well. actually. my car is fine.

815
00:35:11.457 --> 00:35:12.936
but I do need your help
with something else.

816
00:35:12.980 --> 00:35:14.808
What? Who-who are you?

817
00:35:14.851 --> 00:35:16.418
My name is Danny James.

818
00:35:16.462 --> 00:35:18.942
I work with Rafael Ramirez's
defense team.

819
00:35:18.986 --> 00:35:20.857
I figured you'd be more open
to talking to me out here

820
00:35:20.901 --> 00:35:22.250
than up at the ranch.

821
00:35:22.294 --> 00:35:23.686
Look. lady. I don't want
to get involved.

822
00:35:23.730 --> 00:35:25.079
I just want
to ask you a question

823
00:35:25.123 --> 00:35:26.298
about your boss's husband
Noah Sinclair.

824
00:35:26.341 --> 00:35:27.951
Do you have any reason

825
00:35:27.995 --> 00:35:30.476
to believe
that he disliked Lauren Parker?

826
00:35:30.519 --> 00:35:33.435
I'm not talking to you about
the Sinclairs. I need my job.

827
00:35:33.479 --> 00:35:34.871
Well. the word is already out

828
00:35:34.915 --> 00:35:36.525
that your bosses were
doping their horses.

829
00:35:36.569 --> 00:35:37.613
I mean. how much longer
do you think they'll be able

830
00:35:37.657 --> 00:35:39.572
to stay
in the horse racing business?

831
00:35:39.615 --> 00:35:42.444
No idea. but I'm holding on
to my job as long as I can.

832
00:35:44.620 --> 00:35:46.579
I know you like
to help people.

833
00:35:46.622 --> 00:35:48.668
You wouldn't have stopped
for me if you didn't.

834
00:35:48.711 --> 00:35:50.409
I just wonder how
it's gonna sit with you

835
00:35:50.452 --> 00:35:52.193
if Rafael goes to prison
for something he didn't do

836
00:35:52.237 --> 00:35:54.326
when you could have
helped save him.

837
00:35:56.241 --> 00:35:58.417
Remember how the Sinclairs filed

838
00:35:58.460 --> 00:36:00.332
an insurance claim on that
other horse earlier this year?

839
00:36:00.375 --> 00:36:03.509
Gold Rush?
Yeah. Noah Sinclair's horse.

840
00:36:03.552 --> 00:36:07.600
Well. it turns out. Noah blamed
Lauren Parker for its death.

841
00:36:07.643 --> 00:36:10.733
A stable hand overheard Noah
and Garrett fighting about it.

842
00:36:10.777 --> 00:36:13.388
Noah was screaming
that Garrett had to fire Lauren.

843
00:36:13.432 --> 00:36:16.174
Hmm. Do we know
what killed the horse?

844
00:36:16.217 --> 00:36:17.392
The insurance claim lists

845
00:36:17.436 --> 00:36:19.394
cause of death
as renal failure.

846
00:36:19.438 --> 00:36:21.179
Performance-enhancing
drugs can wreak

847
00:36:21.222 --> 00:36:23.181
havoc on kidneys.

848
00:36:23.224 --> 00:36:25.226
If Lauren was doping the horse
without Noah's knowledge.

849
00:36:25.270 --> 00:36:28.229
and it wound up dead.
maybe Noah wanted revenge.

850
00:36:28.273 --> 00:36:30.579
You think he killed a woman
to avenge a horse?

851
00:36:30.623 --> 00:36:33.191
Well. Raf said Noah was
crazy about that horse.

852
00:36:33.234 --> 00:36:35.280
Some people love
their pets even more

853
00:36:35.323 --> 00:36:36.716
than they love
their families.

854
00:36:36.759 --> 00:36:38.108
Think about Judge Grant.
True.

855
00:36:38.152 --> 00:36:39.980
But why kill
Bold Spirit. too?

856
00:36:40.023 --> 00:36:41.634
An eye for an eye.

857
00:36:41.677 --> 00:36:43.201
He wanted
to punish Garrett

858
00:36:43.244 --> 00:36:45.464
for allowing Lauren
to dope his horse.

859
00:36:45.507 --> 00:36:47.727
But why would he let
Bold Spirit burn alive?

860
00:36:47.770 --> 00:36:50.643
That's a brutal way to die.
Maybe he didn't.

861
00:36:50.686 --> 00:36:52.775
Check this out.

862
00:36:53.994 --> 00:36:55.604
And what is this?

863
00:36:55.648 --> 00:36:58.085
A prescription monitoring
database.

864
00:36:58.128 --> 00:37:00.174
Noah's a retired
veterinarian.

865
00:37:00.218 --> 00:37:02.350
A month ago. he ordered a case
of sodium Pentothal.

866
00:37:02.394 --> 00:37:04.657
which is used
to euthanize horses.

867
00:37:04.700 --> 00:37:07.834
He put the horse down
before the fire?

868
00:37:07.877 --> 00:37:09.879
We think so.

869
00:37:09.923 --> 00:37:11.838
Or maybe he bought that
to use in case he needed

870
00:37:11.881 --> 00:37:14.449
to put a horse
out of his misery.

871
00:37:14.493 --> 00:37:16.190
Look. there's no way
we can prove

872
00:37:16.234 --> 00:37:18.279
that he used it
on Bold Spirit now anyway.

873
00:37:18.323 --> 00:37:21.413
There is. actually. if you don't
mind getting your hands dirty.

874
00:37:21.456 --> 00:37:23.284
I don't understand.
What is this?

875
00:37:23.328 --> 00:37:25.373
It's a motion
to exhume Bold Spirit.

876
00:37:26.418 --> 00:37:28.594
Dig him up?
Are you kidding me?

877
00:37:28.637 --> 00:37:30.204
They can't do this. can they?

878
00:37:30.248 --> 00:37:33.860
I'm afraid so.
Judge Grant signed the motion.

879
00:37:33.903 --> 00:37:36.254
Bold Spirit died a horrible
death because of your client.

880
00:37:36.297 --> 00:37:37.820
and now you won't even
let him rest in peace.

881
00:37:37.864 --> 00:37:39.387
We have reason to believe

882
00:37:39.431 --> 00:37:40.606
that Bold Spirit didn't die
in the fire.

883
00:37:40.649 --> 00:37:42.303
What are you talking about?

884
00:37:42.347 --> 00:37:43.870
His body was found
along with Lauren's.

885
00:37:43.913 --> 00:37:47.003
We believe that he was
euthanized with sodium Pentothal

886
00:37:47.047 --> 00:37:48.396
before the fire
was started.

887
00:37:48.440 --> 00:37:51.269
Sodium Pentothal
is a controlled substance.

888
00:37:51.312 --> 00:37:52.835
How would Rafael get
his hands on it?

889
00:37:52.879 --> 00:37:53.967
He didn't.

890
00:37:54.010 --> 00:37:55.664
But your husband did.

891
00:37:58.624 --> 00:38:00.713
This is insane.
First you tried

892
00:38:00.756 --> 00:38:02.280
to pin this on me.

893
00:38:02.323 --> 00:38:04.020
Then you go
after Lauren's reputation.

894
00:38:04.064 --> 00:38:05.195
Now you're accusing Noah.

895
00:38:05.239 --> 00:38:06.806
You're just grasping at straws.

896
00:38:06.849 --> 00:38:08.895
Your husband held Lauren Parker

897
00:38:08.938 --> 00:38:11.289
responsible for
Gold Rush's death.

898
00:38:11.332 --> 00:38:13.726
He asked you to fire her.
but you didn't.

899
00:38:13.769 --> 00:38:15.380
You know your husband.

900
00:38:15.423 --> 00:38:17.512
Do you think
he'd just accept that?

901
00:38:30.177 --> 00:38:32.614
You asked Lauren
to stay in the barn

902
00:38:32.658 --> 00:38:34.660
with Bold Spirit that night.

903
00:38:34.703 --> 00:38:37.358
Garrett. this is insane.

904
00:38:37.402 --> 00:38:40.361
You know I wouldn't
have hurt anyone.

905
00:38:40.405 --> 00:38:43.277
Did Bold Spirit even have colic?

906
00:38:48.804 --> 00:38:51.067
Go ahead. Dig.

907
00:39:09.608 --> 00:39:12.959
Got it. Good news. Thanks.

908
00:39:13.002 --> 00:39:15.962
Noah Sinclair was charged with
the murder of Lauren Parker.

909
00:39:16.005 --> 00:39:18.007
And Rafael?

910
00:39:18.051 --> 00:39:21.533
The judge dismissed the charges.
He even apologized to Rafael.

911
00:39:22.838 --> 00:39:25.188
And TAC brings another winner
across the finish line.

912
00:39:25.232 --> 00:39:26.668
Giddy-up!

913
00:39:26.712 --> 00:39:28.931
No. Taylor. please.
Oh. you're just

914
00:39:28.975 --> 00:39:30.455
jealous you didn't
think of it first.

915
00:39:32.108 --> 00:39:35.677
Uh... may I interrupt?

916
00:39:38.637 --> 00:39:42.597
I'm gonna go somewhere
that's... not here.

917
00:39:44.817 --> 00:39:49.387
♪ Somehow I wound up
right here where I belong... ♪

918
00:39:49.430 --> 00:39:52.390
This is a surprise.

919
00:39:52.433 --> 00:39:55.044
I didn't expect
to see you again.

920
00:39:55.088 --> 00:39:56.959
♪ Waiting here all alone...

921
00:39:57.003 --> 00:39:58.961
I was thinking
about what you said.

922
00:39:59.005 --> 00:40:03.183
and. um. you didn't know
my history.

923
00:40:03.226 --> 00:40:04.097
and I didn't know yours.

924
00:40:04.140 --> 00:40:06.447
I should have asked.

925
00:40:06.491 --> 00:40:08.362
I could have asked. too.

926
00:40:08.406 --> 00:40:10.799
So?

927
00:40:10.843 --> 00:40:15.151
I like being with you...
Marissa.

928
00:40:15.195 --> 00:40:16.849
♪ So easy...

929
00:40:18.154 --> 00:40:21.593
Maybe we could we put our pasts
in the past and start over?

930
00:40:21.636 --> 00:40:25.161
♪ It can be so easy...

931
00:40:25.205 --> 00:40:27.599
That's a lot of pasts.

932
00:40:29.775 --> 00:40:31.211
♪ So easy...

933
00:40:31.254 --> 00:40:34.997
Then maybe we could.
um. just. uh.

934
00:40:35.041 --> 00:40:36.999
stay in the present.

935
00:40:37.043 --> 00:40:38.436
♪ It can be so easy

936
00:40:38.479 --> 00:40:40.438
I'd like that.

937
00:40:40.481 --> 00:40:44.442
♪ Feels like home

938
00:40:44.485 --> 00:40:46.400
Don't care.

939
00:40:46.444 --> 00:40:50.404
♪ Somehow I wound up
right here where I belong. ♪

940
00:40:50.448 --> 00:40:52.319
I-I don't know how to thank you.

941
00:40:52.362 --> 00:40:54.495
Get help. That's all
the thanks I need.

942
00:40:54.539 --> 00:40:56.236
I'm going
to a meeting tonight.

943
00:40:56.279 --> 00:40:57.411
Well. that's
a good start.

944
00:40:57.455 --> 00:40:59.108
And I-I've got
an interview tomorrow

945
00:40:59.152 --> 00:41:00.501
at another stable.

946
00:41:00.545 --> 00:41:02.851
It's just as a stable hand
for now.

947
00:41:02.895 --> 00:41:05.854
but I'll be around horses.
and that's all I want.

948
00:41:05.898 --> 00:41:08.335
And that's what
I want for you. too.

949
00:41:11.817 --> 00:41:13.601
Dr. Bull.

950
00:41:15.081 --> 00:41:16.430
Thank you.

951
00:41:16.474 --> 00:41:18.040
You take care
of yourself. Raf.

952
00:41:31.445 --> 00:41:33.229
Do you think
he'll stay sober?

953
00:41:33.273 --> 00:41:36.276
Well. that is
entirely up to him.

954
00:41:36.319 --> 00:41:38.713
You did everything you could
to give him a shot.

955
00:41:38.757 --> 00:41:41.455
You believed in him
when no one else would.

956
00:41:41.499 --> 00:41:44.980
Oh. yeah. I was right
and you were wrong.

957
00:41:45.024 --> 00:41:47.287
Oh. boy.

958
00:41:47.330 --> 00:41:50.072
I believe I proved
him innocent.

959
00:41:50.116 --> 00:41:51.552
which should count
for something.

960
00:41:51.596 --> 00:41:53.162
Oh. yeah. sure.
but I still think

961
00:41:53.206 --> 00:41:54.729
I should get a discount
on my bill.

962
00:41:54.773 --> 00:41:57.427
given that I was so right
and you were so wrong.

963
00:41:57.471 --> 00:42:00.126
The bill.
Ah. here we go.

964
00:42:00.169 --> 00:42:05.131
The bill. I believe
you should buy me dinner.

965
00:42:05.174 --> 00:42:06.959
Burgers and fries?

966
00:42:07.002 --> 00:42:09.265
You're not
getting off that easy.

967
00:42:15.924 --> 00:42:19.885
Captioning sponsored by
CBS

968
00:42:19.928 --> 00:42:24.150
and TOYOTA.

